    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Differently from other `fooprg` options, `keywordprg` (used for `K` command) supports an ex command:\r\n```\r\n\tWhen the first character is \":\", the command is invoked as a Vim\r\n\tcommand prefixed with [count].\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be useful to be able to specify (via the Neovim API from Lua, or the Lua API, only) a Lua funcref.\r\n\r\nUse case: setting `keywordprg` to `vim.lsp.buf.hover` (or an appropriate wrapper) to avoid having to remap `K` conditionally.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Use case: setting keywordprg to vim.lsp.buf.hover (or an appropriate wrapper) to avoid having to remap K conditionally.\n\nI still want to use both ftplugin's keywordprg and LSP hover, so I map this `nnoremap <C-k> K`. And as https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/24331#issuecomment-1636107198 says, I can also use `v_K`\n\nBut setting keywordprg to use LSP will make those tricks no longer work",
